
    mplayer -vf screenshot  to-be-play-video.mp4.or.avi.or.any.flv
    # hit 's' when you want the screenshot

Then, to take a single shot, make sure that the mplayer window is active (move
the mouse over it if you are using sloppy focus) and press ‘s’. 

    convert input-image  -resize 1024x  -quality 50%  new-name-image



 Create a stereo output from one mono input:

 ffmpeg -i input.mp3 -ac 2 output.m4a

 or with the amerge audio filter:

 ffmpeg -i input.mp3 -filter_complex "[0:a][0:a]amerge=inputs=2[aout]" -map "[aout]" output.m4a

